Supplementary Material

Hanna Choi

5/1/2021

Supp Figure 1. Normalized Metabolomic Data. MetaboAnalyst 5.0 was used to normalize and standardize the metabolomic data in 14 soil samples per horizon.

Supp. Figure 2. Ammonium, orthophosphate, and nitrate levels. Ammonium, orthophosphate, nitrate absorbances were determined using a colorimetric spectrophotometer with 96 well plates. Absorbances were calculated and converted to concentrations of mg per g soil. Statistically significant differences between the control and heated samples are indicated by a bracket and asterisk (Miranda et al., 2001; Rhine et al., 1998; Ringuet et al., 2011).

Supp. Figure 3. SOM Cluster of Metabolites. Self-Organizing Mapping was clustered using MetaboAnalyist 5.0 and indicate 3 clusters where PC1 and PC2 represent 37.6% of the variation.

Supp. Map 1. Mapped Lipids in the Organic Horizon. Mapped via LIPID MAPS Software, the lipidomic data indicates ~ active pathways. No fatty acid reactions were found in either the (a) organic or (b) mineral horizon.

Supp. Map 2. Mapped Lipids in the Mineral Horizon.
